cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses a new deep network architecture for image classification, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The use of neural science and deep learning techniques suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The focus on image classification benchmarks suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The discussion of network architecture and expressive power suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of inference outputs and pathway selection suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques could suggest that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
